f90ac734-4cbf-413f-a090-3723bb8b4eff.0a2a7b87-52b1-46db-a2e0-7cd58a579c0a.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

Inputs\:

Result\:  List of variables that are null or empty strings
f90ac734-4cbf-413f-a090-3723bb8b4eff.1744b18f-4661-4e69-b0eb-6bdcd1927a56.description=
Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

 Flow that wraps RAS script export-policy-get-iter.pl which wraps Ontap API method export-policy-get-iter.

Purpose\: Get a group of Export policy configurations.

Inputs\:
clusterName\: mandatory (specifies endpoint to run API against).
vServerName\: optional (Vserver name)
policyName\: optional (Export policy name)
policyId\: optional (Export policy id.)

Optional inputs restrict the search, if none are given, all export polcites in the cluster are returned.

Eg output (eg inputs were clusterName and vServerName)\:

                        S223000SL7NAS01_root
                        S223000SL7NAS01
                
                
                        5501853106179
                        S223000SL7VOL01
                        S223000SL7NAS01
                
                
                        5501853106177
                        default
                        S223000SL7NAS01

f90ac734-4cbf-413f-a090-3723bb8b4eff.426f7ea9-ba00-48a4-8409-91a6f45692a7.description=
Synopsis

    This operator removes duplicate strings from a list of delimited strings.

Inputs

    list - A delimited list of strings (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specific.
      Default value\: None.

    delimiter - A sequence of one or more characters used to specify a boundary in a data stream (required).
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: Comma (,).

Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; in this case a duplicate string removal, where applicable.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.

<?xml version="1.0"?>
<xsl:stylesheet version="1.0" xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xmlns:xslt="http://xml.apache.org/xslt" exclude-result-prefixes="xslt"> <xsl:output method="text" />
<xsl:template match="results"> <xsl:for-each select="attributes-list/initiator-group-info[vserver='${vsWithAdapterInitiator}' and initiator-group-name='${anIgroup}']"> <xsl:value-of select="initiator-group-os-type/text()"/> <xsl:if test="not(position() = last())"> <xsl:text>#</xsl:text> </xsl:if> </xsl:for-each>
</xsl:template>
</xsl:stylesheet>

<xsl:template match="results"> <xsl:for-each select="attributes-list/fcp-adapter-initiators-info/vserver"> <xsl:value-of select="text()"/> <xsl:if test="not(position() = last())"> <xsl:text>,</xsl:text> </xsl:if> </xsl:for-each>
</xsl:template>

<xsl:template match="results"> <xsl:for-each select="attributes-list/fcp-adapter-initiators-info[vserver='${vsWithAdapterInitiator}']"> <xsl:value-of select="adapter/text()"/> <xsl:text>%</xsl:text> <xsl:for-each select="fcp-connected-initiators/fcp-connected-initiator-info"> <xsl:choose> <xsl:when test="string-length(initiator-group-list/initiator-group-list-info/initiator-group-name/text()) > 0"> <xsl:value-of select="initiator-group-list/initiator-group-list-info/initiator-group-name/text()"/> </xsl:when> <xsl:otherwise> <xsl:text></xsl:text> </xsl:otherwise> </xsl:choose> <xsl:if test="not(position() = last())"> <xsl:text>^</xsl:text> </xsl:if> </xsl:for-each> <xsl:if test="not(position() = last())"> <xsl:text>!</xsl:text> </xsl:if> </xsl:for-each>
